Having finished his preliminary remarks, Cicero proceeds to the proper subject of his treatise, to wit, a discussion of common duties, καθήκοντα, and occupies the remainder of this section in enumerating the several divisions into which his subject naturally falls. We have, therefore, in this passage, an epitome of the whole work.
